File: platform/cli/src/commands/config.ts, lines 475-486 (handleSetPort function)

Current code:
```
if (newPort !== oldPort) {
    await notifyServer({ ... successMessage: 'Server running on port X. Restart to apply port change.' });
  } else {
    console.log(pc.yellow('Restart the MCP server for the port change to take effect.'));
    await notifyServer({ port: options.port, warnIfNotRunning: true });
  }
```

When newPort === oldPort, the else branch fires and prints 'Restart the MCP server for the port change to take effect.' — but no change occurred.

Fix: When newPort === oldPort, print a message like 'Port is already set to <N>.' and skip the restart warning. Only show the restart warning in the newPort !== oldPort branch. The notifyServer call in the else branch can also be removed since no config change occurred.

Do NOT change the behavior of the newPort !== oldPort branch — it correctly shows a restart warning when the port actually changes.
